hillbillies.model

Class WorldObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • hillbillies.model.WorldObject
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Boulder, Log

    public abstract class WorldObject
extends java.lang.Object
    A class of objects that are in the World.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Kevin Algoet & Jeroen Depuydt 1ba Informatica
    Invariants:
  • The weight of each WorldObject must be a valid weight for any WorldObject.
  • This WorldObject can have its position as its position.
  • This WorldObject can have its falling state as its falling state.
    • Notes:
  • Repository link: https://github.com/KivinA/ProjectOGP
  • The name 'WorldObject' would imply that every object inside the World implements this class. However, we only created this class for Boulder and Log, thus the class Unit won't implement this.

                 throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Advance the time of this WorldObject.
        Effect:

      • terminate

        public void terminate()
        Terminate this WorldObject.
        Postcondition:
        The terminated state of this WorldObject is enabled.
        Effects:
      • Set the World of this WorldObject ineffective.
      • Set the position of this WorldObject ineffective.
        • Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - This WorldObject is already terminated.

        public boolean canHaveAsWorld(World world)
        Check whether this WorldObject can have the given World as its World.
        Parameters:
        world - The World to check.
        Returns:
        If this WorldObject is terminated, true if and only if the given World is ineffective. Otherwise, true if and only if the given World is effective and if that World can have this WorldObject as one of its Logs or Boulders.

      • getPosition

        public double[] getPosition()
        Return the position of this WorldObject.
        Returns:
        An ineffective position if the position of this WorldObject is ineffective.
        Returns:
        The number of elements in the resulting array is equal to the number of elements in the position array of this WorldObject.
        Returns:
        Each element in the resulting array is equal to the element in the position array of this WorldObjects at the same index.

      • canHaveAsPosition

        public boolean canHaveAsPosition(int[] coordinates)
        Check whether this WorldObject can have the given position as its position.
        Parameters:
        position - The position to check.
        Returns:
        If this WorldObject is terminated, true if and only if the given position is ineffective. Otherwise, true if and only if the given position is ineffective or if the given position is effective and between the boundaries of the World of this WorldObject, and if the given cube is passable.

      • setPosition

        public void setPosition(double[] position)
                 throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Set the position of this WorldObject to the given position.
        Parameters:
        position - The position for this WorldObject.
        Postcondition:
        The position of this worldObject is equal to the given position.
        Effects:
      • Enable the falling state if the cube beneath the given position is passable.
      • Disable the falling state if it was already enabled and if the z-position of this WorldObject is 0 or if the cube beneath the given position is solid.
        • Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - This WorldObject cannot have the given position as its position.

        public boolean canHaveAsFallingState(boolean isFalling)
        Check whether this WorldObject can have the given falling state as its falling state.
        Parameters:
        isFalling - The falling state to check.
        Returns:
        If the given fallen state is true, true if and only if the cube beneath this WorldObject is passable. Otherwise, true if and only if the z coordinates of this WorldObject is equal to 0 or if the cube beneath this WorldObject is solid.
